---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Submissions"
	description="Contribute a first-person vignette to the Earth Civilization 0.5 Chronicles (1980-2045)."
	pubDate={new Date('February 25 2026')}
>
	<section>
		<h1>Call for Submissions</h1>
		<p>
			Write your "first time" into the <strong>Earth Civilization 0.5 Chronicles</strong>
			(1980-2045).
		</p>

		<h2>One-sentence summary</h2>
		<p>
			We are building a chronicle that combines verifiable milestones with everyday vignettes,
			documenting the transition from the late mechanical age to the digital era - and then the AI
			era. Official timelines keep the headlines. Ordinary details disappear unless we write them
			down.
		</p>

		<h2>Why we invite you</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Because real change shows up first in daily life: the phone ringing, cassette tapes, video
				halls, dial-up, search engines, recommendations, and now AI at work.
			</li>
			<li>
				Because details fade quickly: in a few years you may remember "it happened", but not the
				sounds, prices, waiting, awkwardness, or excitement.
			</li>
			<li>
				Because we want to record how technology shaped ordinary lives - and that requires many
				voices from many places.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>What you get</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>Byline:</strong> your name, pen name, or anonymous credit (your choice), plus a short
				bio/link (optional).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Preservation:</strong> your memory becomes part of a long-term, structured archive - not a
				disposable post.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Editing support:</strong> we can help with structure and clarity, and mark facts "to
				verify", while keeping your voice.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Optional collaboration:</strong> strong pieces may become a series, an interview, or
				chapter material (with confirmation).
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>What we are looking for</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>First-person vignettes:</strong> one scene is enough (300-1500 words is ideal; shorter is
				welcome).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Evidence-friendly stories:</strong> photos, receipts, manuals, device models, screenshots,
				old emails, links (you may redact).
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Real "how it worked" details:</strong> what was hard, what you hacked around, what it
				cost, who taught you.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>Home/school/workplace scenes:</strong> the more specific, the better.
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Submission template</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>Title (one line)</li>
			<li>Time & place (example: 1998-2001, Jinan, China)</li>
			<li>Story (300-1500 words)</li>
			<li>Optional evidence + permission to quote (yes/no)</li>
			<li>Byline preference: real name / pen name / anonymous</li>
			<li>Best contact method (email)</li>
		</ol>

		<h2>How to submit</h2>
		<p>
			Email: <a href="mailto:jxy88886@gmail.com">jxy88886@gmail.com</a>
		</p>

		<hr />

		<h1>征稿（中文）</h1>
		<p>
			把你的“第一次”写进<strong>《地球文明0.5编年史》</strong>（1980-2045）。
		</p>

		<h2>一句话说明</h2>
		<p>
			我们正在写一部“可查证的年代节点 + 可感知的日常切片”的编年史，记录人类从机械余晖走向数字化，再
			被 AI 重新塑形的全过程。大历史会被写进年鉴，但普通人的细节不会——除非你来写。
		</p>

		<h2>为什么邀请你投稿</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>真正的变化往往先发生在生活里：电话铃、磁带、录像厅、拨号上网、搜索、推荐算法、以及今天的 AI。</li>
			<li>细节会迅速消失：几年后你可能记得“发生过”，但记不住当时的声音、价格、等待、尴尬与兴奋。</li>
			<li>我们想写清“技术如何落到普通人的日常、工作与命运里”，这需要来自不同城市与家庭的真实经验。</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>投稿你能获得什么</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>署名/笔名/匿名：文章发布时标注作者，可附一句简介与链接（可选）。</li>
			<li>长期保存：你的记忆会被整理进结构化档案，而不是很快被信息流淹没。</li>
			<li>编辑支持：可协助润色结构、补充背景、标记【待核】事实，但不替换你的声音。</li>
			<li>深度合作机会：优秀稿件可扩展成系列、访谈或进入正式章节素材库（事先沟通确认）。</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>我们最想收的稿</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>第一人称的小事：一个场景就够（300-1500 字最佳，短也可以）。</li>
			<li>有“物证”的故事：照片、票据、说明书、设备型号、截图、旧邮件、旧网站链接等（可打码）。</li>
			<li>真实细节：它怎么用、哪里麻烦、怎么绕过去、当时花多少钱、谁教你的。</li>
			<li>家庭/学校/工作现场：越具体越好。</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>投稿格式（复制模板即可）</h2>
		<ol>
			<li>标题（1 句话）</li>
			<li>时间与地点（例如：1998-2001，山东济南）</li>
			<li>正文（300-1500 字；短也可以）</li>
			<li>可选物证（照片/票据/截图/型号/链接）+ 是否允许引用</li>
			<li>署名方式：实名 / 笔名 / 匿名</li>
			<li>联系方式：邮箱</li>
		</ol>

		<h2>如何投稿</h2>
		<p>
			邮箱：<a href="mailto:jxy88886@gmail.com">jxy88886@gmail.com</a>
		</p>

		<h2>边界与承诺</h2>
		<ul>
			<li>可以匿名、可以改名、可以隐去单位/人物信息。</li>
			<li>不做政治立场争论：聚焦技术、科学、人文、经济与日常生活。</li>
			<li>不确定就写“不确定”：我们宁可标注【待核】，也不强行编确定答案。</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</Layout>
